     1Рєњ# mdBook-specific features Рђд
     3Рєњ## Hiding code lines
     5РєњThere is a feature in mdBook that lets you hide code lines by prepending them with a specific prefix.
     6Рєњ
     7РєњFor the Rust language, you can prefix lines with `# ` (`#` followed by a space) to hide them [like you would with Rustdoc][rustdoc-hide].
     8РєњThis prefix can be escaped with `##` to prevent the hiding of a line that should begin with the literal string `# ` (see [Rustdoc's docs][rustdoc-hide] for more details)
     9Рєњ
    10Рєњ[rustdoc-hide]: https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/rustdoc/write-documentation/documentation-tests.html#hiding-portions-of-the-example
    11Рєњ
    12Рєњ```bash
    13Рєњ# fn main() {
    14Рєњ    let x = 5;
    15Рєњ    let y = 6;
    16Рєњ
    17Рєњ    println!("{}", x + y);
    18Рєњ# }
    19Рєњ```
